data.enText: to change the position or order of things; to change your position

data.chText: 我们重新摆放了卧室里的家具。
data.enText: We've rearranged the furniture in the bedroom.
She rearranged herself in another pose.

data.chText: 重新安排；改变时间（或日期、地点）
data.enText: to change the time, date or place of an event

data.chText: 我们把会议改到下周二下午两点好吗？
data.enText: Can we rearrange the meeting for next Tuesday at 2?

simple_means.memory_skill: re 重新 + arrange 安排；排列 → 重新安排

tr: put into a new order or arrangement
example: rearrange the furniture in my room

value.def: If you rearrange things, you change the way in which they are organized or ordered.

example.ex: When she returned, she found Malcolm had rearranged all her furniture...
example.tran: 她回家时，发现马尔科姆把她所有的家具都重新摆放了。

example.ex: A waiter was rapidly rearranging tables for the big group.
example.tran: 一个服务生正在麻利地为这一大帮人重新布置餐桌。

value.tran: 重整；重新安排；重新排列

value.def: If you rearrange a meeting or an appointment, you arrange for it to take place at a different time to that originally intended.

example.ex: You may cancel or rearrange the appointment...
example.tran: 你可以取消约会或是重新安排约会时间。

example.ex: The meeting on 31 October is rearranged for 30 January.
example.tran: 10月31日的会议重新安排到了1月30日。
